<br>
new satellite goes up to detect liquid in mars, scientists then also use this prototype to search for more frozen over lakes in Antartica, a large lake is found deep below the ice that couldn't be detected by technology.<br>
 ten scientists set out to probe the lake in the middle of nowhere in search of basic bacterial lifeforms or fossils of prehistoric origin.Most of the scientists are european eviormentalists the american scientist is a cia agent in search of oil since america is collapsing since the oil in the middle east is almost totally depleted.<br>
 Oil was found... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=psyco@polykarbonbbs>psyco</A> at: 5/15/03 4:00:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zerothyme>zero thyme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/16/03 1:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Black Ice</span><hr size=1> I guess my question is what is the driving conflict?<br>
<br>
Just having scientists looking for fossils, etc. and an undercover agent/oil expert isn't enough to be compelling.<br>
<br>
Scientists bonding together to eliminate the CIA agent before he can report oil found would be a conflict.<br>
<br>
CIA Agent ordered to kill the whole group if they found any worth while discovery that could stop the procurement of the oil would be a conflict.<br>
<br>
The agent falling in love with one of the scientists would be a conflict.<br>
<br>
Having to put aside their differences and suspicions to make it back out alive after they have accidentally woken up some ancient evil would be a conflict.<br>
<br>
Greed and Politics verses Ivory Tower Idealism is a good beginning though. Keep working on it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=psyco@polykarbonbbs>psyco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/16/03 4:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.neonwheels.com/preacher/covers/57.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Black Ice</span><hr size=1> -they are stuck in a middle of a storm. when finding out that there is oil, they all agree to keep this covered since the cost to pump oil out of the antartic would be less profitable in the first place. two days later during the storm one scientist discover's about the identity of the american and reports it. the cia agent is forced undercaptivity with his own gun which the scientist found. Hansel shroder the belgian marine biologist who had been involed in vietnam protests during his studies in college has fears that the american goverment may consider global warming in the far future as a last resort to get to the oil.<br>
